<h1 style="float: left; margin-top: 30px; margin-left: 40px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 2em;">RDRC</h1>
<p style="float: left; margin: 30px 0px 0px 60px;">
    A ripoff comic of Ruby conferences,<br>
    bad drawing, and weak humor.
</p>

<div style="clear: both; width: 100%; padding: 10px; text-align: center;">
    <h2><%= h @alt %></h2>
    <div>
        <% [["<< First", @first], ["< Prev", @prev], ["Next >", @next], ["Last >>", @last]].each do |label, link| %>
            <% next if link.nil? %>
            <%= link_to label, rdrc_path(:id => File.basename(link)[/\A\d{8}/]) %>&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <% end %>
    </div>
    <img src="<%= @image %>" alt="<%= h @alt %>" title="<%= h @title %>">
    <div>
        <% [["<< First", @first], ["< Prev", @prev], ["Next >", @next], ["Last >>", @last]].each do |label, link| %>
            <% next if link.nil? %>
            <%= link_to label, rdrc_path(:id => File.basename(link)[/\A\d{8}/]) %>&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <% end %>
    </div>
</div>

<p style="margin-left: 40px; text-align: left;">
    Q: What does RDRC stand for?<br>
    A: Red Dirt RubyComic, of course!
</p>
